    "name": "KG2Vec",
    "description": "Knowledge Graph Embedding methods aim to represent entities and relations within a knowledge base as vectors or points in a continuous vector space. These approaches have demonstrated promising results on tasks such as link prediction, entity recommendation, question answering, and triplet classification. A limitation noted is that few methods can compute low-dimensional embeddings of very large knowledge bases without specific requirements.",
